Despite the reverence accorded to Gazi Pir, there are ongoing debates and controversies surrounding his historical existence and the exact nature of his contributions. Some historians argue that the figure of Gazi Pir may be a composite of several individuals who played a role in the Islamization of Sylhet. Others suggest that the legends and folktales associated with Gazi Pir may have been embellished over time, making it difficult to separate fact from fiction.

