One of the primary challenges in studying the life of Gazi Pir is the lack of contemporaneous historical evidence. Most of the information about Gazi Pir comes from oral traditions and later historical accounts, which can be subject to interpretation and bias. This has led to a range of opinions among scholars regarding the historical accuracy of the stories associated with Gazi Pir.

